Before running the script /DistanceBasedApproaches.ipynb
**********************************************************************************

#prerequisites 
#pip install bert-serving-server  # server
#pip install bert-serving-client  # client, independent of `bert-serving-server`

#to run this we need to start bert server from the command prompt
#got to anaconda prompt
#activate virtual environment , if you are using a virtual environment for running this code
#run the command
#bert-serving-start -model_dir C:\Users\ASUS\NLP\embeddings\uncased_L-12_H-768_A-12 -num_worker 1

#C:\Users\ASUS\NLP\embeddings\uncased_L-12_H-768_A-127 this is the folder to which i downloaded the pretrained BERT, you can download it from

#https://github.com/google-research/bert#pre-trained-models




Running the Web application:
*************************************************************************************************


1)	Go to the Anaconda command prompt
2)	Activate virtual environment if you are running the app from virtual environment
3)	Install flask if it is not already installed in your system, using the command
‘pip install flask’

4)	If running on linux, export FLASK_APP environment variable. (All the files for web app is in the WebApp folder)
export FLASK_APP= app_folder_path\app.py
In windows machine
set FLASK_APP=app_older_path\app.py
eg: set FLASK_APP=C:\QAsystem\app.py
5)	Go the app folder, and run the command ‘flask run’



Link for embeddings: 
https://nlp.stanford.edu/projects/glove/> [Accessed 27 August 2020].
<https://code.google.com/archive/p/word2vec/> 